<blockquote>Did Jesus exist? Was he who he claimed he was? What do historians, modern and ancient, say?

</blockquote>First let's see what modern historians say about Jesus.
<h2><strong>Modern</strong> historians</h2>According to the Wikipedia article <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Historicity_of_Jesus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the historicity of Jesus</a>, "<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">Virtually all scholars of antiquity accept that Jesus was a historical figure</span>". They vary on the details but <span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">"two key events are subject to "almost universal assent", namely that</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," title="Baptism of Jesus" href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baptism_of_Jesus">Jesus was baptized</a><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">by</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," title="John the Baptist" href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_the_Baptist">John the Baptist</a><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">and</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," title="Crucifixion of Jesus" href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crucifixion_of_Jesus">crucified</a><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">by order of the Roman Prefect</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," title="Pontius Pilate" href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pontius_Pilate">Pontius Pilate</a><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">.</span>"

Wikipedia goes on to summarize:
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">Historian</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><a class="mw-redirect" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," title="Michael Grant (author)" href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Grant_(author)">Michael Grant</a><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">asserts that if conventional standards of historical textual criticism are applied to the</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>New Testament<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">, "we can no more reject Jesus' existence than we can reject the existence of a mass of</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>pagan personages<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"> whose reality as historical figures is never questioned."</span>

</blockquote>
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">Virtually </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><strong>all</strong></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>biblical scholars<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">and</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>classical historians<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">see the theories of his non-existence as effectively refuted,</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"> and in modern scholarship, the Christ myth theory </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><em>[that Jesus was a myth]</em></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"> is a</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>fringe theory<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">and finds virtually </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><strong>no</strong></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"> support from scholars.</span>

</blockquote>Noted agnostic scholar Bart Ehrman say<span style="caret-color: #c8ccd1; color: #c8ccd1; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">s: </span>
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #c8ccd1; color: #c8ccd1; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">"He certainly existed, as virtually every competent scholar of antiquity, Christian or non-Christian, agrees, based on certain and clear evidence." ((B. Ehrman, 2011</span><span style="caret-color: #c8ccd1; color: #c8ccd1; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><i style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">Forged&nbsp;: writing in the name of God</i> ISBN<span style="caret-color: #c8ccd1; color: #c8ccd1; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">&nbsp;</span>978-0-06-207863-6<span style="caret-color: #c8ccd1; color: #c8ccd1; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">. p. 256-257</span>))

</blockquote>So the most basic historical facts that are beyond debate are:
<ol>Jesus lived</ol>
<ol>Jesus was baptized by John</ol>
<ol>Jesus was crucified by Pontius Pilate</ol>Let's move on and see what we can learn about him based on ancient historical accounts.
<h2>Ancient historians</h2><a href="https://thyreon.com/the-gospels-are-greco-roman-historical-biographies/">Technically the Gospel accounts of the Bible count as Greco-Roman historical biographical accounts.</a> And we get the most details about the life of Jesus from the gospels. But since some biased people say that we can not use the Bible to discuss the Bible, this list will concentrate on what secular historians have written.
<h3><strong>Flavius Josephus</strong></h3>Flavous Josephus was a historian who lived from 37-100 AD. He was basically <strong>neutral</strong> to the christians. In his book <em>Antiquities of the Jews</em> volume 18, chapter 9, paragraph 3 he writes:
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">3. Now there was about this time </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Jesus, a wise man, if it be lawful to call him a man; for he was a doer of wonderful works, a teacher of such men as</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> receive the truth with pleasure. He drew over to him both many of the Jews and many of the Gentiles. He was [the] Christ. And when Pilate, at the suggestion of the principal men amongst us, had condemned him to the cross,</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> those that loved him at the first did not forsake him; for he appeared to them alive again the third day;</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> as the divine prophets had foretold these and ten thousand other wonderful things concerning him. And the tribe of Christians, so named from him, are not extinct at this day.</span>

</blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Although </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">the vast majority have considered it to be authentic</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">((</span>Richard Bauckham<span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">"FOR WHAT OFFENSE WAS JAMES PUT TO DEATH?" in</span><span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><i style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration: none">James the Just and Christian origins</i><span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">by Bruce Chilton, Craig A. Evans 1999</span><span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>ISBN<span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">&nbsp;</span>90-04-11550-1<span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #222222; color: #222222; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">pages 199–203</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">)) there are a few who debate the </span>authenticity<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> of it saying think that there has been </span>interpolation<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">s in the text by later </span>Christian<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> sources. In any case we can learn that: </span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">There was a man named Jesus.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">He was considered wise, a teacher.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">He was a miracle worker.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">He had many followers, both Jews and Gentiles.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Jesus was famous and claimed to be the </span>Christ<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">The leaders of the people hated him.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Pontius Pilate condemned him.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">He was crucified.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">His followers </span>didn't<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> stop following him.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Allegedly he appeared to his followers after his death, specifically on the third day.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">There were prophecies that he is said to have fulfilled.</span></li>
</ul><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">In volume 20, chapter 9 paragraph 1 mentions:</span>
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">...Festus was now dead, and Albinus was but upon the road; so he assembled the sanhedrim of judges, and brought before them the brother of Jesus, who was called Christ, whose</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">name was James, and some others, [or, some of his companions]; and when he had formed an accusation against them as breakers of the law, he delivered them to be stoned:</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">...</span>

</blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">No scholar questions this section. But the interesting part is that this section only </span>makes<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> sense if "Jesus who was called Christ" was already introduced in the previous section. </span>

<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">This text shows:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Jesus existed.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Jesus was famous and claimed to be the Christ.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">He had a brother named James (Jacob).</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">The leaders of the people were hostile to him too.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">James was executed by stoning.</span></li>
</ul>
<h3><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Tacitus</span></h3><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">Tacitus lived 56-120 AD and was </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><strong>hostile</strong></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> to the Christians. In his book </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"><em>Annals</em></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> volume 15, chapter 44, Tacitus writes:</span>
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">...Consequently, to get rid of the report [that Nero himself was behind the </span>fire<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none"> in Rome], Nero fastened the guilt and inflicted the most exquisite tortures on a class hated for their abominations, called Christians by the populace. Christus, from whom the name had its origin, suffered the extreme penalty [euphemism for </span>crucifixion<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">] during the reign of Tiberius at the hands of one of our procurators, Pontius Pilatus, and a most mischievous superstition, thus checked for the moment, again broke out not only in Judaea, the first source of the evil, but even in Rome, where all things hideous and shameful from every part of the world find their centre and become popular. Accordingly, an arrest was first made of all who pleaded guilty; then, upon their information, an immense multitude was convicted, not so much of the crime of firing the city, as of hatred against mankind. Mockery of every sort was added to their deaths. Covered with the skins of beasts, they were torn by dogs and perished, or were nailed to crosses, or were doomed to the flames and burnt, to serve as a nightly illumination, when daylight had expired. Nero offered his gardens for the spectacle, and was exhibiting a show in the circus, while he mingled with the people in the dress of a charioteer or stood aloft on a car. Hence, even for criminals who deserved extreme and exemplary punishment, there arose a feeling of compassion; for it was not, as it seemed, for the public good, but to glut one man's cruelty, that they were being destroyed.</span>

</blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">From this account we can learn that:</span>
<ul>
 	<li>Jesus existed.</li>
 	<li>He was known as the Christ.</li>
 	<li>There was something extraordinary about him ["<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: auto; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.3); -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; display: inline !important; float: none">mischievous superstition</span>"]</li>
 	<li>He was executed by crucifixion</li>
 	<li>Pontius Pilate existed and was responsible for the crucifixion.</li>
</ul>We can also learn that:
<ul>
 	<li>Christianity spread rapidly and widely.</li>
 	<li>Christians were hated for not sacrificing to Caesar ["abominations"].</li>
 	<li>Christians were severely persecuted.</li>
 	<li>Christians did not deny Jesus even when faced with death.</li>
 	<li>Christians were tortured and executed in the most horrible ways. So bad that even Romans started to think it was over the top.</li>
</ul>The fact that Christians were facing death so bravely was because they strongly believed in the resurrection. In the case of the disciples their conviction was not because of what someone else had told them but because of what they themselves had witnessed. They had no reason to die for their own lie. So this is a strong evidence for the resurrection being a true event.
<h2>Mara bar Serapion</h2>Mara bar Serapion<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">was a</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Stoic philosopher from<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"> the</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Roman province of Syria<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">. He</span> wrote<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">a letter </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">to his son, </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">which most scholars date to shortly after 73 AD during the first century</span>. The way he phrases things shows scholars that Mara bar Serapion was not a Christian and he seems to be <strong>neutral</strong> toward them.

<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">His letter refers to the unjust treatment of "three wise men": the murder of</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Socrates<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">, the burning of</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Pythagoras<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,">, and the execution of "the wise king" of the Jews</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,"> and how in all three cases the wrongdoing resulted in the future punishment by God</span>.

Here is the relevant text:
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">What else can we say, when the wise are forcibly dragged off by tyrants, their wisdom is captured by insults, and their minds are oppressed and without defense? What advantage did the Athenians gain from murdering</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Socrates<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">? Famine and plague came upon them as a punishment for their crime. What advantage did the men of</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Samos<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">gain from burning</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Pythagoras<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">? In a moment their land was covered with sand. </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><em>What advantage did the Jews gain from executing their wise king?</em></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"> It was just after that their kingdom was abolished. God justly avenged these three wise men: the Athenians died of hunger; the Samians were overwhelmed by the sea and </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><em>the Jews, desolate and driven from their own kingdom, live in complete dispersion</em></span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">. But Socrates is not dead, because of</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Plato<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">; neither is Pythagoras, because of the statue of</span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>Juno<span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122">; </span><span style="caret-color: #202122; color: #202122"><em>nor is the wise king, because of the "new law" he laid down.</em></span>

</blockquote>The punishment for the Jews he refers to is the destruction of Jerusalem in 70 AD, tree years before. The only known person that was considered wise and a "King of the Jews" whom the Jews themselves executed before 70 AD was Jesus.

What can we learn from this?
<ul>
 	<li>These details corroborates the existence of Jesus.</li>
 	<li>Jesus was considered wise.</li>
 	<li>Jesus was known as a king.</li>
 	<li>The stories about Jesus was well known around the Roman Empire by 73 AD, only about 40 years after his death.</li>
 	<li>Jesus had a new teaching, a "new law", which is consistent with what the New Testament teaches.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Suetonius</h2>Suetonius was a Roman historian who lived from 69-122 AD. He was clearly <strong>hostile</strong> to Christians.

In his book <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Lives_of_the_Twelve_Caesars/Claudius#25" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Lives of the Twelve Cesars: Divus Claudius chapter 25</a> he mentions:
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>Since the Jews constantly made disturbances at the instigation of Chrestus</span>((Chrestus was an alternative spelling of Christ.))<span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>,</span><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:> he expelled them from Rome.</span><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:><span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span>

</blockquote>It talks about how Claudius expelled the Jewish Christian's from Rome, which corroborates Acts 18:2 that tells that Aquila and Pricilla were expelled from Rome by Claudius. This happened in 41 or 49 AD according to scholars which means that in only about 8-16 years the Christian message had spread and gotten so popular that the emperor of the known world deemed them to be a nuisance.

Suetonius also wrote a <a href="https://en.m.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Lives_of_the_Twelve_Caesars/Nero#16" target="_blank" rel="noopener">biography about emperor Nero</a> where he mentions the Christians.
<blockquote><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>Punishment was inflicted on the Christians, a class of men given to a new and mischievous superstition.</span>

</blockquote><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>From this we learn that by the year 64 when this happened, the </span>Christian<span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>s had </span>returned to <span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>Rome and that </span>they<span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:> </span>had new teachings<span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:> </span><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>that the Romans thought</span><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:> were </span>"mischievous<span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>((</span><span style="caret-color: rgb(32, 33, 34); color: rgb(32, 33, 34); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont," segoe ui roboto lato helvetica arial sans-serif font-size: font-style: normal font-variant-caps: font-weight: letter-spacing: orphans: auto text-align: start text-indent: text-transform: none white-space: widows: word-spacing: rgba background-color: rgb text-decoration: display: inline float:>The word translated as "mischievous" above is</span><span style="caret-